hopobject.body: What university do you go to? adiramedica.com Dejen Gebremeskel was the closest finisher to Farah in the 5,000m in London last year. Since then his strategy for trying to overcome the Briton has been to move up a distance, and it returned a quick dividend. On his debut over 10,000m earlier this year he clocked a world-leading time of 26 min 51.02 sec. He has beaten Farah in the past and done so having lost a shoe mid-race.
